    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The various insignia of a Nahua tlahtoani (ruler) in postclassic central Mexico, including the xiuhhuitzolli (turquoise mosaic diadem) and the xiuhtilmahtli (turquoise cape), usually tenixyoh ("with eyes on the edge").</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
